[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    174[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mStep 1: Classify message intent.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m When a new patient message arrives, the first thing we do is figure out what they're asking about. This classification determines what context we need to gather and which prompt template to use. A refill request needs the patient's current medication list. An appointment question needs their upcoming schedule. A symptom question needs recent visit history. Getting this wrong means the draft will be grounded in irrelevant context, which means the provider will have to rewrite it from scratch. For routine messages, simple keyword and pattern matching works well. You don't need an LLM for this step.[K
