[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    235[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    236[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mStep 3: Assemble the prompt.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m This is where the magic happens (and where most implementations get it wrong). The prompt has three parts: a system prompt that defines behavior constraints, the patient context assembled in Step 2, and the actual patient message. The system prompt is the most important piece. It tells the model what it can and cannot do. Without explicit constraints, the model will try to be maximally helpful, which in a medical context means offering diagnoses, suggesting treatments, and generally doing things that only a licensed provider should do. The system prompt is your primary safety mechanism (Guardrails is your secondary one).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    237[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    238[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m```[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    239[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mFUNCTION build_prompt(message_text, intent, context, provider_preferences):[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    240[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // Load the base system prompt template from S3[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    241[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // This template defines the model's role, constraints, and tone[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    242[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    system_prompt = load_from_s3("prompts/system-prompt-v2.txt")[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    243[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    244[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // The system prompt should contain instructions like:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    245[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // - You are drafting a response for a healthcare provider to review[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    246[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // - Never diagnose conditions or suggest new treatments[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    247[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // - Never recommend medications not already in the patient's active list[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    248[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // - Never promise specific timelines unless confirmed in the context[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    249[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // - Keep responses warm, professional, and concise (under 150 words)[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    250[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // - Address the specific question asked; do not volunteer additional information[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    251[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // - If the question requires clinical judgment, say the provider will follow up[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    252[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    253[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m    // Load provider-specific tone preferences if available[K
